def _get_time_bins(self, ax):
    if not isinstance(ax, DatetimeIndex):
        raise TypeError(
            "axis must be a DatetimeIndex, but got "
            f"an instance of {type(ax).__name__}"
        )

    if len(ax) == 0:
        binner = labels = DatetimeIndex(data=[], freq=self.freq, name=ax.name)
        return binner, [], labels

    first, last = _get_timestamp_range_edges(
        ax.min(), ax.max(), self.freq, closed=self.closed, base=self.base
    )

    # Retrieve unique values for ax
    ax_values = ax.unique()

    # Generate range while handling ambiguous times
    binner, labels = self._generate_with_ambiguous_time(
        first, last, ax.tz, ax.name, ax_values
    )

    # Call _adjust_bin_edges to handle adjustments
    binner, bin_edges = self._adjust_bin_edges(binner, ax_values)

    # Generate bins considering the adjustments
    bins = lib.generate_bins_dt64(ax_values, bin_edges, self.closed, hasnans=ax.hasnans)

    # Handle label and bin adjustments
    labels = self._adjust_labels(binner, labels, bins, ax.hasnans)

    return binner, bins, labels
